</m:mrow>
<m:mrow>
<m:mn>0</m:mn>
<m:mo>.</m:mo>
<m:mn>3</m:mn>
</m:mrow>
</m:mfrac>
<m:mo>=</m:mo>
<m:mn>0</m:mn>
<m:mo>.</m:mo>
<m:mn>6</m:mn>
<m:mn>7</m:mn>
</m:math>
</p>
    <p>Note that we are substituting the event "X&#160;&lt;&#160;4" for event B, and the event "X&#160;&gt;&#160;2" for event A.</p>
    <p>Also note that the only way that (X&#160;&lt;&#160;4) and (X&#160;&gt;&#160;2) can happen together is if X = 3.</p>
</example>
